In symptomatic acute HIV infection (acute retroviral syndrome), the viral load is usually very high (>>1000 copies/mL). If acute HIV infection is clinically suspected and there is a detectable but low viral load, please contact the laboratory for interpretation.  It is recommended that any NEW positive HIV-1 viral load result, in the absence of positive serology, be confirmed by submitting a new sample FOR HIV-1 PCR, in addition to serological testing.

Greatly elevated serum protein with IgG levels >2000 mg/dl may cause  interference with CMV IgM results.  If current infection is suspected, submit follow-up serum in 2-3 weeks.
